SIMPLE: impenitent
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Impenitent
<hw>Im*pen"i*tent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>impaenitens</ets>; pref. <ets>im-</ets> not + <ets>paenitens</ets>
penitens: cf. F. <ets>imp⟦eacute⟧nitent</ets>. See
<er>Penitent</er>.]</ety> <def>Not penitent; not repenting of sin; not
contrite; of a hard heart.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧They . . . died
<xex>impenitent</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Milton.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧A careless and
<xex>impenitent</xex> heart.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Bp. Hall.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Impenitent</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Impenitent
<hw>Im*pen"i*tent</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who is not
penitent.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Impenitently</ent>⟦br⟧
